title: 1.10.6: BAD BLOCK ON MAINNET
body:
#### System information

Geth version: `1.10.6`
OS & Version: docker on linux
Commit hash : (if `develop`)

ERROR[07-23|10:03:35.132]
########## BAD BLOCK #########
Chain config: {ChainID: 1 Homestead: 1150000 DAO: 1920000 DAOSupport: true EIP150: 2463000 EIP155: 2675000 EIP158: 2675000 Byzantium: 4370000 Constantinople: 7280000 Petersburg: 7280000 Istanbul: 9069000, Muir Glacier: 9200000, Berlin: 12244000, London: 12965000, Engine: ethash}

Number: 12881667
Hash: 0xa5773dc655c46b6e5aa183ed1f6f22e5e22e7b9391f2af645e2ffb7cb8b9988c
I just downgraded geth to version 1.0.3 and it works now
Can you provide more logs?
I don't keep the log, which is very long and it basically contains information about transactions and block 12881667

It's may relevant with the corrupted database, or the new release may contain the consensus issue.
Do you mind to switch it back to the 1.10.6 to see if it's reproducible?
I can't upgrade it again, it's our production service, many services depend on it, but I can try to run geth 1.10.6 from scratch with full sync mode.
Do you run 1.10.6 geth? I think others may be experiencing the same issue

I just found that snapshot sync mode breaks node.

geth shouldn't set it default.

Block on etherscan: https://etherscan.io/block/12882625
My (snap synced) node accepted it correctly
I got the same thing but on ropsten the release before the consensus fix.

I don't use snapshot sync mode

at first I use on 1.10.3/1.10.5

```
--syncmode=full
--snapshot=false
```

and upgrade to 1.1.0.6, it generates snapshot state with high cpu usage, and the errors appear

```
--syncmode=full
```

downgrade to 1.10.3 it works now but a few hours later, the errors appear again.

and I add `--snapshot`=false` param, it's been running for 10 hours , and geth syncs correctly now.

so I think this error is because snapshot sync mode is turned on

I also get the same error on mainnet. The error block seems to be different. This happened after upgrading to 1.10.6.


@leeheejoo which version do you upgrade from?

@safinbot you disable the snapshot in your previous runs. After upgrade to 1.10.6, your node start to generate the missing snapshot in the background. And in the mean time the generated partial snapshot is used(it should be correct though).

@rjl493456442 


I updated from version 1.10.2 to version 1.10.6.

After the above error occurred, the state information was received again after applying removedb in version 1.10.6.

There was no problem when receiving state information again. And now it's working fine.

Any problems updating from version 1.10.2 to version 1.10.6? Or is there a config item to edit?

@leeheejoo have you disabled the snapshot when you run the 1.10.2? 
From the running log, your node has been generating snapshot for 42 hours, I guess the snapshot is always enabled right?

`1|geth | INFO [07-26|00:47:08.646] Generating state snapshot root=8caf33..5d807b at=9f6664..b03a14 accounts=88,020,926 slots=311,222,245 storage=26.33GiB elapsed=42h44m20.108s eta=25h54m2.756s
`

@rjl493456442 

the error occurred when updating the chain from 1.10.2 to 1.10.6 and catching up with the chain, which is about 300,000 blocks behind.

I would like to know if I really need to disable the snapshot function? If I don't do I get an error?

No config changes have been made. I guess I didn't disable the snapshot function.

Please tell me what item to disable the snapshot function in the config file. I am using the config file.

thank you.
@leeheejoo Snapshot is supposed to be working! Just want to figure out the reason for your corrupted database.
